ğŸŸ¢ Level 1 â€” Basics (Concept Building)
1.	Match all strings that contain only lowercase letters.
    [a-z]+
Example: "hello" âœ… "Hello" âŒ
2.	Match a string that starts with an uppercase letter and ends with a period (.).
    [A-Z][a-z]+\.
Example: "Hello." âœ… "hello." âŒ
3.	Match all strings that are valid integers (positive or negative).// for all +/- floating ^-?\d+(\.\d+)?, ? for optional, \. for single dot
Example: "-42" âœ… "003" âœ… "4.2" âŒ
    (^-)?\d+
4.	Match a 10-digit number (only digits).
Example: "9876543210" âœ… "98765abc" âŒ
    \d{10}
5.	Match a string that has exactly 3 lowercase letters followed by 2 digits.
Example: "abc12" âœ… "ab12" âŒ
    [a-z]{3}\d{2}
6.	Match a word that contains the substring "cat" anywhere.
Example: "educate", "concatenate" âœ… "dog" âŒ// .* any 0 or more char
    .*(cat).*
7.	Match a string that contains no digits.
Example: "abc!" âœ… "a1" âŒ
    ^\D*

8.	Match a string that starts and ends with the same letter.
Example: "level" âœ… "abc" âŒ
    ^([a-zA-Z]).*\1$             //.* or or more char \1 means the same of start ^([a-zA-Z]) and $ any String
