ğŸ§  Level 1 â€” Complex Pattern Composition
1.	Match a floating-point number â€” supports optional sign, optional decimal, and optional exponent (e.g., -12.5, 3., .5, 2e10).
2.	Match a valid time (24-hour format) â†’ e.g., 00:00 to 23:59.
3.	Match dates with separators -, /, or ., like 2025-10-10, 10/10/2025, 10.10.2025.
4.	Match a US/Indian phone number â€” optional country code (+91, +1), optional spaces or dashes.
5.	Match a valid IPv4 address â€” ensure each octet is 0â€“255 (no 256).
6.	Match valid IPv6 addresses (e.g., 2001:0db8:85a3::8a2e:0370:7334).
7.	Match valid MAC address â€” formats like 00:1A:C2:7B:00:47 or 00-1A-C2-7B-00-47.
8.	Match valid URL (http, https, ftp) â€” with optional www., domain, path, query.
9.	Extract domain name from an email (use capturing groups).
10.	Validate a credit card number (Visa, MasterCard, AmEx patterns only).
