ğŸ§© Level 3 â€” Capturing, Backreferences & Nested Patterns
21.	Extract text inside parentheses but not nested ones.
Example: from "A(B(C)D)E", match "B(C", not "C" or outer "A(B(C)D)E".
22.	Match palindromic words of even or odd length (using backreference symmetry).
23.	Validate a string that is a valid JSON number (handle -, decimals, exponent, no leading zeros).
24.	Extract content between HTML tags ignoring nested tags (use lazy quantifiers).
25.	Validate balanced parentheses (only possible with recursive patterns in PCRE).
